<DOC><DOCNO> AP890220-0143 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-20-89 2309EST</FILEID><FIRST>u i AM-Honduras-Prison 1stLd-Writethru a0635 02-20 0354</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Honduras-Prison, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0635,0361</SECOND><HEAD>Bomb Rips Through Interior Minister's Office After Prison Occupation</HEAD><HEAD>Eds: LEADS with 7 grafs to UPDATE with bomb explosion outside officesof govt minister who ordered prison occupation. Pick up 5th pvs, `The policestatement...'</HEAD><BYLINE>By FREDDY CUEVAS</BYLINE><BYLINE>The Associated Press</BYLINE><DATELINE>TEGUCIGALPA, Honduras (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A bomb exploded outside the officesof Interior and Justice Minister Enrique Ortez Colindres on Monday,a day after he ordered police occupation of a prison whose officialsare accused of corruption.   No injuries were reported when the four sticks of dynamiteexploded at 7:10 p.m., damaging the building and shattering thewindows of the Honduran Telecommunications Co. building across thestreet, police sources said.   No one immediately claimed responsiblity.   Police on Sunday occupied the nation's largest prison after thegovernment accused prison officials of corruption, drug traffickingand trying to foment a riot by 1,500 inmates, officials said Monday.   The Public Security Forces said in a statement that it haddetected ``a dangerous escalation of sedition and rioting that wouldhave occurred today (Monday) with the alleged participation ofseveral officials of the Central Penitentiary'' in Tegucigalpa, thecapital.   It said prison officials and ``highly dangerous delinquents''were planning a riot ``that would produce a massive escape ofprisoners in detriment to national security and tranquility.''   Ortez Colindres told The Associated Press he temporarilysuspended prison director Marco Tulio Mendieta. Ortez Colindres saidhe named Maj. David Mendoza Garcia, schooled in prisonadministration in Argentina, as the facility's acting director.   The police statement said an investigation detected ``an elevatedand proven administrative corruption, trafficking in drugs, sales ofexit permits to very dangerous criminals, incitements to armedrevolt by the guards, an indiscriminate possession of arms insidethe prison,'' and other irregularities.   More than 200 members of the crack Cobra police squadron occupiedthe facility late Sunday, it said. The measures were taken to ensurepublic order, and 60 prison guards and officials were arrested, itsaid.   Officials said the takeover was peaceful and reported nocasualties.   The Central Penitentiary houses inmates convicted of violentcrimes, including homicide, rape and drug trafficking.</TEXT></DOC>